theorem Topology.frontier_eq_empty_iff_isOpen_and_isClosed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier A = (∅ : Set X) ↔ (IsOpen A ∧ IsClosed A) := by
  constructor
  · intro hFrontEmpty
    -- First, translate the definition of the frontier.
    have hFrontDef :
        frontier A = closure A \ interior A :=
      (Topology.frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A))
    -- From `frontier A = ∅` we deduce `closure A ⊆ interior A`.
    have hSub : closure A ⊆ interior A := by
      intro x hxClos
      by_contra hNotInt
      have hxFront : x ∈ frontier A := by
        have : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := And.intro hxClos hNotInt
        simpa [hFrontDef] using this
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [hFrontEmpty] using hxFront
      cases this
    -- Hence `closure A = interior A`.
    have hClosEqInt : (closure A : Set X) = interior A :=
      Set.Subset.antisymm hSub interior_subset
    -- From this we get `A = interior A = closure A`.
    have hIntEqA : interior A = A := by
      apply Set.Subset.antisymm
      · exact interior_subset
      · intro x hxA
        have hxClos : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
        have : (x : X) ∈ interior A := by
          simpa [hClosEqInt] using hxClos
        exact this
    have hClosEqA : closure A = A := by
      simpa [hIntEqA] using hClosEqInt.symm
    -- Conclude that `A` is both open and closed.
    have hOpen : IsOpen A := by
      simpa [hIntEqA] using (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior A))
    have hClosed : IsClosed A := by
      simpa [hClosEqA] using (isClosed_closure (s := A))
    exact And.intro hOpen hClosed
  · rintro ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩
    exact
      Topology.frontier_eq_empty_of_isOpen_and_isClosed
        (A := A) hOpen hClosed
